to the editor re the land of lewis and clark editorial aug 10 as a western south dakota native and mother of three i know how important it is that at least a few small areas of our national grasslands are protected as wilderness these areas with imagination provoking names like red shirt and first black canyon are truly special places as you put it they merit stronger protection as one of the last big remnants of authentic prairie margaret m messerli rapid city sd aug 11 2003

